      • model

        static timeseries.models.arima.ArimaModel model(TimeSeries observations,
                                                ModelOrder order)
        Create a new ARIMA model from the given observations and model order. This constructor sets the model Arima.FittingStrategy to unconditional sum-of-squares and the seasonal cycle to one year.
        Parameters:
        observations - the time series of observations.
        order - the order of the ARIMA model.
        Returns:
        a new ARIMA model from the given observations and model order.

      • model

        static timeseries.models.arima.ArimaModel model(TimeSeries observations,
                                                ModelOrder order,
                                                TimePeriod seasonalCycle)
        Create a new ARIMA model from the given observations, model order, and seasonal cycle. This method sets the model Arima.FittingStrategy to unconditional sum-of-squares.
        Parameters:
        observations - the time series of observations.
        order - the order of the ARIMA model.
        seasonalCycle - the amount of time it takes for the seasonal pattern to complete one cycle. For example, monthly data usually has a cycle of one year, hourly data a cycle of one day, etc... However, a seasonal cycle may be an arbitrary amount of time.
        Returns:
        a new ARIMA model from the given observations, model order, and seasonal cycle.

      • model

        static timeseries.models.arima.ArimaModel model(TimeSeries observations,
                                                ModelOrder order,
                                                Arima.FittingStrategy fittingStrategy)
        Create a new ARIMA model from the given observations, model order, and fitting strategy. This method sets the seasonal cycle to one year.
        Parameters:
        observations - the time series of observations.
        order - the order of the ARIMA model.
        fittingStrategy - the strategy to use to fit the model to the data. Maximum-likelihood estimates are typically preferred for greater precision and accuracy, but take longer to obtain than conditional sum-of-squares estimates.
        Returns:
        a new ARIMA model from the given observations, model order, and fitting strategy.

      • model

        static timeseries.models.arima.ArimaModel model(TimeSeries observations,
                                                ModelOrder order,
                                                TimePeriod seasonalCycle,
                                                Arima.FittingStrategy fittingStrategy)
        Create a new ARIMA model from the given observations, model order, seasonal cycle, and fitting strategy.
        Parameters:
        observations - the time series of observations.
        order - the order of the ARIMA model.
        seasonalCycle - the amount of time it takes for the seasonal pattern to complete one cycle. For example, monthly data usually has a cycle of one year, hourly data a cycle of one day, etc... However, a seasonal cycle may be an arbitrary amount of time.
        fittingStrategy - the strategy to use to fit the model to the data. Maximum-likelihood estimates are typically preferred for greater precision and accuracy, but take longer to obtain than conditional sum-of-squares estimates.
        Returns:
        a new ARIMA model from the given observations, model order, seasonal cycle, and fitting strategy.

      • model

        static timeseries.models.arima.ArimaModel model(TimeSeries observations,
                                                ModelCoefficients coeffs,
                                                TimePeriod seasonalCycle)
        Create a new ARIMA model from the given observations, model coefficients, and seasonal cycle. This constructor sets the model Arima.FittingStrategy to conditional sum-of-squares followed by maximum likelihood.
        Parameters:
        observations - the time series of observations.
        coeffs - the coefficients of the model.
        seasonalCycle - the amount of time it takes for the seasonal pattern to complete one cycle. For example, monthly data usually has a cycle of one year, hourly data a cycle of one day, etc... However, a seasonal cycle may be an arbitrary amount of time.
        Returns:
        a new ARIMA model from the given observations, model coefficients, and seasonal cycle.

      • model

        static timeseries.models.arima.ArimaModel model(TimeSeries observations,
                                                ModelCoefficients coeffs,
                                                TimePeriod seasonalCycle,
                                                Arima.FittingStrategy fittingStrategy)
        Create a new ARIMA model from the given observations, model coefficients, seasonal cycle, and fitting strategy.
        Parameters:
        observations - the time series of observations.
        coeffs - the coefficients of the model.
        seasonalCycle - the amount of time it takes for the seasonal pattern to complete one cycle. For example, monthly data usually has a cycle of one year, hourly data a cycle of one day, etc... However, a seasonal cycle may be an arbitrary amount of time.
        fittingStrategy - the strategy to use to fit the model to the data. Maximum-likelihood estimates are typically preferred for greater precision and accuracy, but take longer to obtain than conditional sum-of-squares estimates.
        Returns:
        a new ARIMA model from the given observations, model coefficients, seasonal cycle, and fitting strategy.

      • pointForecast

        TimeSeries pointForecast(int steps)
        Description copied from interface: Model
        Produce a time series of point forecasts from this model up to the given number of steps ahead.

        To obtain additional information about the forecast, such as prediction intervals, use the Model.forecast(int, double) method and the resulting Forecast object.

        Specified by:
        pointForecast in interface Model
        Parameters:
        steps - the number of time periods ahead to forecast.
        Returns:
        a time series of point forecasts from this model up to the given number of steps ahead.

      • forecast

        Forecast forecast(int steps,
                  double alpha)
        Description copied from interface: Model
        Produce a new forecast up to the given number of steps with the given α significance level for computing prediction intervals.
        Specified by:
        forecast in interface Model
        Parameters:
        steps - the number of time periods ahead to forecast.
        alpha - the probability that a future observation will fall outside the associated (1 - α)100% prediction interval, given that the model is "correct". Note that the correctness of the model often comes with a high degree of uncertainty and this should be taken into account when making decisions. In other words, the provided prediction intervals will often be overly optimistic.
        Returns:
        a new forecast up to the given number of steps ahead with the given significance level.
